CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 10, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Yum, Yum!  It must be good to Jacqueline Strothers, daughter of Sgt. and Mrs. John Strothers of 833 Shawnee Street.  In a pensive mood, Jackie is wondering what she will get for her valentine."
TitMainTitle: Jacqueline "Jackie" Strothers posed with two fingers in mouth, in front of moire background, Harris Studio
